# Cross-platform parity (BytzGo)

BytzGo has THREE surfaces that do NOT share UI code. A user-facing change is not
"done" until it is applied to every surface it touches, and all affected builds
are rebuilt/redeployed.

| Surface | Where | Notes |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Backend / API | `backend/server.ts`, `backend/**` | Shared source of truth (data + money logic). Change once. Deployed to Render from GitHub `main`. |
| Web app | `src/**` (React + TypeScript) | Separate from mobile. |
| Mobile app | `mobile/lib/**` (Flutter / Dart) | One codebase → builds BOTH iOS and Android. |

## Rules

1. **Mirror UI/logic changes in BOTH `src/` (web) and `mobile/lib/` (Flutter).**
   The web React app and the Flutter app are independent — a feature added to one
   must be added to the other unless the user explicitly says one platform only.
2. **iOS + Android share `mobile/lib/`.** A Dart change is automatically on both.
   It only "shows on one platform" because of a stale build or per-OS native config.
3. **Per-OS native config / assets are NOT shared — update both when relevant**
   (permissions, app icon, identity, deep links, push). Example bug: the branded
   launcher icon existed for Android (`res/mipmap-*/ic_launcher.png`) but iOS still
   shipped the Flutter placeholder in `ios/Runner/Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset`.
   - iOS: `mobile/ios/Runner/Info.plist`, `Assets.xcassets`, `Runner.xcodeproj`
   - Android: `mobile/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`, `res/`, `build.gradle`
4. **After changing, rebuild every affected target** (a build that wasn't rebuilt is
   the #1 reason a change "didn't reach" a platform):
   - Web/backend: pushed to GitHub `main` → Render auto-deploys
   - iOS: `flutter build ipa` (bump `pubspec.yaml` build number) → upload to App Store
   - Android: `flutter build appbundle` → upload to Play

## Parity map (known web ↔ mobile pairs)

| Concern | Web | Mobile (Flutter) |
|---------|-----|------------------|
| Rider console | `src/components/rider/RiderApp.tsx` | `mobile/lib/features/rider/rider_shell.dart` |
| Customer app | `src/components/customer/**`, `src/App.tsx` | `mobile/lib/features/customer/**` |
| Paystack checkout | `src/lib/paystackCheckout.ts` | `mobile/lib/features/wallet/paystack_*.dart` |
| Wallet / payments | `src/lib/walletTopup.ts` | `mobile/lib/features/wallet/wallet_repository.dart` |

## Done-checklist for any feature/fix

- [ ] Backend updated (if data/logic) — `backend/server.ts`
- [ ] Web updated — `src/**`
- [ ] Mobile updated — `mobile/lib/**` (covers iOS + Android)
- [ ] Per-OS native config/assets updated on BOTH iOS and Android if relevant
- [ ] All affected targets rebuilt (Render push, iOS build, Android build)
